abstract:
Penalized regression methods are important when the number p of covariates exceeds the number of samples n. The LASSO allows to select variables in optimal ways. We will discuss recent results in three directions: 
(a) variable preselection - to start with a manageable set of covariates - based on a sequential implementation of the LASSO with increasing lists of predictors, exploiting the freezing property of corresponding cross-validation curves; 
(b) measurement error bias correction - because in many applications covariates are subject to measurement error - without the need of repeated measurements in generalized linear models; 
(c) instability of variable screening - due to random partitions in cross validation - in Cox proportional hazard models with interactions. 

In collaboration with Linn Cecilie Bergersen, Oystein Sorensen, Clara Cecilie Gunther, Sylvia Richardson, Ingrid K. Glad, Magne Thoresen, Ismal Ahmed, Hayat Mohammed
